{
  "stem": "21482.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't really know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my-- I always went to visit my mother and my grandparents in the shul for High Holy Days.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother's parents did not belong to the same temple as my father's parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were, you know, like almost across the street, so I would go and make my rounds, go from one temple to another, especially on Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I used to make apples.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I used to put cloves in the apples and bring it to my grandmother's for Yom Kippur, because, of course, they fasted.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They used to smell the apples.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The smell was supposed to revive them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think probably Passover.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I loved Passover because at Passover we went to my-- our maternal grandparents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for a long time, I was the only child there because my youngest cousin wasn't born yet and the other cousins who lived in Berlin did not come for Passover.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was the only one, and I was to sit next to my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Passover, the Seder was conducted in the bedroom.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The table was brought to the back so my grandfather could sit on all the down pillows and recline, just-- just like you're supposed to do.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I would sit next to him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was probably two years old when I started to ask the four questions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember, you know, how much-- how proud I was, because they made such a big deal about me being able to do that.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When you're an only child and an only grandchild, I don't know, it's very special.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember a lot of helping, you know, when my mother was making-- when she was baking, I used to lick the spoon.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
